 Sunday Shodip, the 19-year-old suspected Ibadan serial killer, has been rearrested by operatives of the Oyo State police command. The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Olugbenga Fadeyi, confirmed the development to the Tribune. “The suspect has been rearrested and is currently in police custody,” he said. Shodipe is suspected to have killed about six women at Akinyele Local Government Area of the state and had escaped from the Mokola police station on Tuesday August 11.